|YK0#|YKB The Berserker Guild|000

|GK0Berserkers are melee warriors who turn injury and combat pressure into
Fury. When Fury peaks, it can erupt as Frenzy: a rapid series of attacks
that spends the accumulated rage against the Berserker's current enemy.|000

|GK0Experienced Berserkers can restrain Frenzy and let excess Fury become
Madness. Madness increases their violence and resilience, but its highest
levels carry serious risks. The |CKBbvent|GK0 command can clear Fury and
Madness after combat.|000

|YK0##|YKB Rank, Vex, and scars|000

|GK0Berserkers advance through a separate Berserker Rank earned in combat.
Each Rank grants Vex that can be trained through the Blood, Momentum, and
Defiance branches. Permanent scars record exceptional ordeals and can later
be awakened with Flare.|000

|YK0##|YKB Equipment and joining|000

|GK0Berserkers may use light, medium, or heavy armour, including shields.
Their training pit lies west of the plain on Darkwind's southern shore.
Join there with |CKBjoin berserker|GK0 when you meet the guild requirements.|000

